    dek: `Every child actor comes with a parent, and that parent is present all day, every day. Get the relationship right and they're your greatest asset — the person who knows the child best and can help you get the performance. Get it wrong and they can derail your set. Here's how to turn stage parents into allies and set the boundaries that keep everyone, especially the child, on track.`,
